1
00:00:01,770 --> 00:00:02,770
I'm so sorry.

2
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:03,940
(Episode 40)

3
00:00:06,810 --> 00:00:09,380
I'm afraid you need to prepare yourself.

4
00:00:10,620 --> 00:00:11,720
Doctor.

5
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:14,720
Please save my dad.

6
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:17,020
But you said the surgery went well,
didn't you?

7
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,290
The head trauma is more severe
than we thought.

8
00:00:19,890 --> 00:00:24,400
No, that can't be!
I can't lose my dad like this.

9
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,970
Doctor, I'm begging you.

10
00:00:28,370 --> 00:00:30,670
Please, just save my dad. Please?

11
00:00:31,970 --> 00:00:32,970
I'm very sorry.

12
00:00:36,780 --> 00:00:37,780
(Korea University Hospital)

13
00:00:57,330 --> 00:00:58,500
I'm afraid...

14
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:01,500
you need to prepare for the worst
for Mr. Oh Bok Gil.

15
00:01:02,570 --> 00:01:03,600
Dad.

16
00:01:21,820 --> 00:01:22,990
No.

17
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:38,040
Wait a minute.

18
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,270
Her name is Jang Mi, right?

19
00:01:40,610 --> 00:01:42,470
Oh Jang Mi, I really need to talk to you.

20
00:01:42,910 --> 00:01:46,080
How on earth do you look exactly like me?
Who are you?

21
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:55,720
Where did she go?

22
00:02:02,530 --> 00:02:03,530
Oh Jang Mi?

23
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,200
What's your problem?

24
00:02:11,540 --> 00:02:13,000
Where did she disappear to so fast?

25
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,010
Where is she?

26
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:19,410
Was I just seeing things?

27
00:02:19,410 --> 00:02:20,810
That's not it.

28
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:22,380
She looked just like me.

29
00:02:23,050 --> 00:02:24,050
Oh Jang Mi!

30
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:26,350
Don't run away! Come out!

31
00:02:26,350 --> 00:02:28,850
Stop hiding and show yourself!

32
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:30,660
Oh Jang Mi!

33
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:40,100
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

34
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:46,740
I wonder what on earth happened
to Jang Mi's father's cell phone.

35
00:02:51,210 --> 00:02:52,310
Oh Bok Gil.

36
00:02:53,980 --> 00:02:56,780
This might just be the crucial evidence.

37
00:02:58,420 --> 00:03:00,620
Tossing this anywhere
would be a huge mistake.

38
00:03:31,580 --> 00:03:32,580
Detective,

39
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:35,490
did you have any luck
finding Jang Mi's father's cell phone?

40
00:03:36,890 --> 00:03:39,460
- I've been thinking...
- About what?

41
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:42,490
Could you tell me
Ssangkal's last known whereabouts?

42
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,200
After the banner incident,

43
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,600
with those guys trying to hurt Jang Mi
and all,

44
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:49,430
I can't help but suspect him.

45
00:03:49,570 --> 00:03:52,770
Trust me, we're going crazy over here,
juggling this with other cases.

46
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:55,070
- I'll be in touch. Just wait.
- Hey, Detective, wait!

47
00:03:56,740 --> 00:03:57,740
What did the detective say?

48
00:03:58,810 --> 00:04:00,280
And who is this Ssangkal?

49
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:04,450
What's all this about
someone trying to hurt Jang Mi?

50
00:04:05,350 --> 00:04:06,380
Sit down, Mom.

51
00:04:11,820 --> 00:04:12,860
Tell me...

52
00:04:13,690 --> 00:04:15,090
about that young woman, Oh Jang Mi.

53
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,900
Was she involved in some kind of crime?

54
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:20,830
Is that how your dad got caught up
in this mess?

55
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:21,900
It's not like that, Mom.

56
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:25,600
- It sounds exactly like that to me.
- Mom.

57
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:29,270
I know you're beside yourself
with worry about Dad,

58
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:31,410
but our first concern
should be for the victim.

59
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:34,610
- Until the police figure something out...
- Figure what out?

60
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:37,050
Ssangkal? What kind of name is that?

61
00:04:37,050 --> 00:04:38,220
Even his name sounds scary.

62
00:04:39,550 --> 00:04:44,060
Anyway, this thing with that Jang Mi girl
just feels wrong.

63
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:46,620
Mom, don't you trust my judgment?

64
00:04:47,830 --> 00:04:50,130
Jang Mi is the woman I love.

65
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:53,600
When you talk about her that way,
it hurts me too, Mom.

66
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:56,800
You raised me better than that,
didn't you?

67
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,400
Just have a little faith in me...

68
00:04:59,140 --> 00:05:00,240
and be patient.

69
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:03,610
I don't know what to think.

70
00:05:17,820 --> 00:05:20,390
That sounds just like twin telepathy.

71
00:05:22,830 --> 00:05:23,900
I'm a twin?

72
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:26,060
I'm a twin?

73
00:05:27,330 --> 00:05:28,370
No way!

74
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:31,670
There are tons of people who look alike.
Why would I be a twin?

75
00:05:40,810 --> 00:05:42,180
But she really did look just like me.

76
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:44,750
This is driving me crazy!

77
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:45,750
Shit.

78
00:05:48,150 --> 00:05:49,150
Right.

79
00:05:49,820 --> 00:05:52,890
I have to find out
if we're really twins or what.

80
00:05:56,330 --> 00:06:00,100
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

81
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:31,730
How's our Jun Ho's office coming along?

82
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,000
"Our" Jun Ho?

83
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:40,640
There's something
I've been meaning to ask you.

84
00:06:41,510 --> 00:06:43,270
You used to hate Chef Kang Jun Ho so much.

85
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:46,310
Why are you suddenly helping him
and treating him like your own son?

86
00:06:46,410 --> 00:06:49,080
And on top of that,
you've made him a general manager?

87
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:53,450
Well...

88
00:06:53,450 --> 00:06:56,150
I'm not sure if I should be
telling you this.

89
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:57,320
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

90
00:06:57,490 --> 00:06:58,520
What is it?

91
00:07:00,090 --> 00:07:01,090
Hwa Young.

92
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:03,930
Do we really need to have secrets
between us?

93
00:07:04,830 --> 00:07:07,770
I promised I would carry
all your burdens, forever.

94
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:11,370
Even if the world were to end,
I'm on your side.

95
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:13,810
You're right.

96
00:07:13,810 --> 00:07:16,370
I suppose there's no reason
to hide it from you.

97
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:18,440
The truth is...

98
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:21,910
Yes, Kang Jun Ho is my son.

99
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:26,250
I only recently found out myself.

100
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:28,150
All this time,

101
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:31,590
I had many chances to tell you,
but I kept it a secret because...

102
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:37,300
when it came to you,
I wanted to remain a woman, not a mother.

103
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:40,460
No, I wanted you to see me as a woman.

104
00:07:41,270 --> 00:07:42,370
Then...

105
00:07:44,270 --> 00:07:45,940
before the whole thing with the twins,

106
00:07:47,340 --> 00:07:48,710
you'd already had a son?

107
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:52,310
Yes, I was very young.

108
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,710
The boyfriend I had back then...

109
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:58,950
took off the second
I told him I was pregnant.

110
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:02,150
I was struggling to get by...

111
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:05,920
and couldn't afford formula,
so I had to secretly give him up.

112
00:08:07,060 --> 00:08:10,700
And I swore I'd succeed
and come back for him no matter what.

113
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,730
And I'm almost there.

114
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:17,940
Kang Hyuk,
I need you to help my Jun Ho out, okay?

115
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:19,940
Please.

116
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:28,880
How do you like the office?

117
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:31,120
Is everything to your liking?

118
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,520
Yes.

119
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:36,390
It's great, Manager Lee.

120
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:39,060
Good.

121
00:08:39,990 --> 00:08:42,390
If you run into any trouble,
don't hesitate to discuss it with me.

122
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:44,900
I'll do everything I can to help you.

123
00:08:49,770 --> 00:08:52,340
Is it a good time to go get
the CEO's approval?

124
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:56,040
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

125
00:08:56,170 --> 00:08:59,380
You've already organized everything
and drafted a proposal?

126
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:01,010
Team Leader Jin helped me.

127
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:02,810
It was nothing.

128
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:04,680
It's my job to help you, of course.

129
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:08,890
Mom! You'll never guess
who I just ran into.

130
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:13,160
If it isn't the handsome Chef Jun Ho.

131
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,990
- Seo Rin.
- Oh, right.

132
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:16,930
I mean, General Manager Kang Jun Ho.

133
00:09:17,190 --> 00:09:19,260
I needed to talk to you
and General Manager Kang...

134
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:22,730
about the project team.
What perfect timing.

135
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,370
Do you have a moment,
General Manager Kang?

136
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,200
- Yes.
- A meeting?

137
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:30,710
My blood sugar is crashing.
I need a caffeine infusion.

138
00:09:31,540 --> 00:09:34,180
Team Leader Jin, get me a double espresso.

139
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:38,480
- Director Ma, you should get that your...
- I'll have an iced americano, too.

140
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:40,180
And you, General Manager Kang?

141
00:09:41,050 --> 00:09:42,050
I'm fine, thank you.

142
00:09:43,220 --> 00:09:44,990
Yes, I'll go get them now.

143
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,900
What were you saying earlier?
Who did you say you ran into?

144
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,800
It's not like anything is confirmed yet.

145
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:56,700
There's no need to air my business
in front of Jun Ho.

146
00:10:01,710 --> 00:10:02,710
It's okay, you can answer it.

147
00:10:03,710 --> 00:10:04,710
And have a seat over there.

148
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:08,610
- Let's just wait for Team Leader Jin.
- Yes.

149
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:15,990
- Yes, Mother.
- Jun Ho.

150
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:18,360
What on earth are we going to do?

151
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:19,790
Is something wrong?

152
00:10:26,730 --> 00:10:29,900
- What?
- You look at him like he's your son.

153
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:31,800
Why are you staring at him so fondly?

154
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:35,340
My phone's ringing.

155
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,640
Hello, this is Chae Hwa Young.

156
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:41,950
It's about your father. I'm so worried.

157
00:10:47,650 --> 00:10:49,090
Hwa Young, it's me.

158
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:54,490
- Yes?
- Who is it?

159
00:10:58,660 --> 00:11:00,970
- I'm listening.
- My wife...

160
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:05,400
went to the hospital and asked,
and she heard the man I hit with my car...

161
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,610
is not going to make it.

162
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:10,040
If he dies...

163
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:11,480
What do you mean he won't make it?

164
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:14,210
If...

165
00:11:15,010 --> 00:11:16,680
if that person dies,

166
00:11:16,950 --> 00:11:18,120
your father's case...

167
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:21,320
will be changed to vehicular manslaughter.

168
00:11:22,020 --> 00:11:23,290
What are we going to do?

169
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:29,030
Mom. I'll call you right back.

170
00:11:29,930 --> 00:11:32,700
- Let's talk later.
- I'm really losing my mind.

171
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:34,500
Who am I supposed to talk to?

172
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,570
You can't.

173
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:40,740
You can't do that.
I'm in a meeting right now.

174
00:11:41,210 --> 00:11:42,510
I'll call you back.

175
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,450
Mom, what do you mean, "you can't?"

176
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:52,350
And Jun Ho, what was that about
"someone not going to make it?"

177
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:55,290
It's rude to pry into other people's
personal business like that.

178
00:11:55,350 --> 00:11:56,350
Seriously...

179
00:11:57,560 --> 00:12:00,560
- Are you two ganging up on me?
- I'm sorry,

180
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:04,300
could we possibly postpone
the meeting until tomorrow?

181
00:12:04,660 --> 00:12:07,570
Yes, that's fine. Something urgent
just came up on my end too.

182
00:12:16,170 --> 00:12:19,040
Mom, it looks like something's
happened to Jun Ho.

183
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:21,910
- What?
- I overheard him on the phone...

184
00:12:21,910 --> 00:12:23,680
talking about an all-night interrogation.

185
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:25,580
And he just said
someone is not going to make it.

186
00:12:25,580 --> 00:12:26,620
What's that about?

187
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:27,920
Seo Rin.

188
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:31,990
Are you really serious about things
with General Manager Kang?

189
00:12:32,060 --> 00:12:33,160
Of course I am.

190
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:37,190
This is the first time I've ever been
this serious about a guy. You know that.

191
00:12:37,830 --> 00:12:39,430
You're right, that's true.

192
00:12:40,330 --> 00:12:44,440
Anyway, go on back to work.
I have some work to do myself.

193
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:47,670
But how am I supposed
to ask about the twin?

194
00:12:47,770 --> 00:12:49,570
Go on, I told you I'm busy.

195
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:51,940
Okay, fine.

196
00:13:00,350 --> 00:13:02,550
Surely Professor Kang
wouldn't tell his family...

197
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,160
the truth about that day, would he?

198
00:13:06,190 --> 00:13:08,160
I can't let him tell them.

199
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:12,260
I have to go calm him down.

200
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:20,910
Professor Kang, can we meet right now?

201
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:25,710
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

202
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:31,520
Jang Mi,

203
00:13:31,820 --> 00:13:34,890
you looked so distraught
when I saw you earlier.

204
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:38,420
Your father will definitely pull through.

205
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:42,390
So you have to take care of yourself too.

206
00:13:48,530 --> 00:13:52,170
Okay.
So let's say I have an identical twin.

207
00:13:57,470 --> 00:13:59,310
(Korea University Hospital)

208
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:06,580
Oh Jang Mi.

209
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:10,290
But why did Mom hit
Oh Jang Mi's dad with a wrench?

210
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:13,690
Burying the wrench is destroying evidence.

211
00:14:14,090 --> 00:14:15,690
Why?

212
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:18,600
Did Mom...

213
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:21,570
try to kill Oh Jang Mi's dad?

214
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:25,600
What should I do?

215
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:30,710
That's it. Rather than asking Mom,

216
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:34,280
it might be faster to meet her
and ask her myself.

217
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:42,020
You look exhausted.

218
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:44,090
If he dies...

219
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,420
If he dies,

220
00:14:47,790 --> 00:14:50,360
- what will happen to me?
- Nam Bong, you have your wife,

221
00:14:50,660 --> 00:14:52,730
the lawyer, Han Young Ja.

222
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,700
Lawyer Han would never let you
get arrested.

223
00:14:56,970 --> 00:14:58,340
And neither would I.

224
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:01,710
Do you really think I'd stand by
and let that happen?

225
00:15:03,210 --> 00:15:05,110
- Hwa Young.
- Professor Kang.

226
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:09,410
If the police catch us meeting like this,

227
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:11,550
things will get very complicated.

228
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:14,550
So please, refrain from calling me.

229
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:18,420
And you absolutely cannot
tell anyone else.

230
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:20,790
I know.

231
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:24,530
But you and I are the only ones
who know the truth.

232
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:27,360
I feel so frustrated,
like I'm going to lose my mind.

233
00:15:28,330 --> 00:15:29,570
I couldn't help it.

234
00:15:29,570 --> 00:15:31,700
You think I don't understand how you feel?

235
00:15:33,970 --> 00:15:35,840
I feel like I'm going crazy too.

236
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:39,640
Hwa Young.

237
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:42,580
The investigation will be over soon.

238
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:44,780
What's the point of my influence...

239
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:46,920
if not to help you at a time like this?

240
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:48,550
You mean it?

241
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:52,060
Thank you, Hwa Young.

242
00:15:53,190 --> 00:15:54,190
You don't need to thank me.

243
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:58,730
It's crystal clear that you're innocent.

244
00:16:29,630 --> 00:16:32,400
(Intensive Care Unit)

245
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:37,900
That man...

246
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,870
I feel like I've seen him
somewhere before.

247
00:16:47,110 --> 00:16:50,980
- Grandpa.
- You were in your room. Where did you go?

248
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:52,280
I just...

249
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:53,950
stepped out for a second.

250
00:16:54,850 --> 00:16:55,850
Mom?

251
00:16:56,290 --> 00:16:58,860
- I don't know.
- Go find your mother and hurry back.

252
00:16:59,190 --> 00:17:00,960
We have something important to discuss.

253
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,560
Got it.

254
00:17:09,530 --> 00:17:11,800
I know I've seen that man
somewhere before.

255
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:19,610
(Yeongseo Police Chief)

256
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,650
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

257
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:23,950
Chief.

258
00:17:24,620 --> 00:17:25,950
This is Chae Hwa Young.

259
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:30,050
We were supposed to go golfing.
Why haven't I heard from you?

260
00:17:30,620 --> 00:17:32,320
And I miss you, Chief.

261
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:35,060
Oh my, Chief.

262
00:17:36,330 --> 00:17:37,560
You'll really do that for me?

263
00:17:38,430 --> 00:17:39,760
That was fast.

264
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:43,130
If it's too much trouble,
you don't have to pull any strings.

265
00:17:43,570 --> 00:17:45,670
It wasn't driving under the influence,
and it wasn't a hit-and-run either.

266
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,240
It's just a simple traffic accident,
and he even turned himself in.

267
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:52,880
I only mentioned it
because it was really not a big deal.

268
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:57,080
Okay. Please set a date
for us to go golfing.

269
00:17:57,550 --> 00:17:58,820
Okay, talk to you later.

270
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:04,560
It's unlikely Oh Bok Gil
will make it through the night.

271
00:18:06,090 --> 00:18:08,030
That bastard held on for a long time.

272
00:18:08,860 --> 00:18:11,530
Anyway, it's all finally over.

273
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:13,860
Congratulations.

274
00:18:20,370 --> 00:18:21,370
Yeom San Wol? What is it?

275
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:25,740
The Chairman said he wants you
to come home to talk. Didn't you hear?

276
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:27,640
Father did?

277
00:18:29,410 --> 00:18:30,580
Fine, whatever.

278
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:41,190
Today is a special occasion.

279
00:18:41,930 --> 00:18:45,260
- A toast, everyone.
- A special occasion?

280
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:53,600
Mrs. Yeom and I...

281
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:56,770
have decided to get married.

282
00:18:56,770 --> 00:18:58,010
What the...

283
00:18:58,010 --> 00:18:59,780
- Grandpa!
- Father!

284
00:19:00,010 --> 00:19:02,750
You've been living together all this time.
What's this about getting married?

285
00:19:03,180 --> 00:19:04,520
Just keep living the way you are.

286
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:08,950
There's no need to get so hostile.
Don't worry. I'm not legally marrying her.

287
00:19:09,220 --> 00:19:11,760
We're just going to have a small ceremony
with the family and live together.

288
00:19:11,820 --> 00:19:14,790
- How's it different from your life now?
- Seo Rin.

289
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:17,790
Your grandpa has been very lonely.

290
00:19:18,260 --> 00:19:22,000
I'm starting to step back from work,
and I'd like to find a little happiness.

291
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,400
Shit.

292
00:19:23,670 --> 00:19:24,840
Whatever.

293
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,740
- Seo Rin.
- Just let her be.

294
00:19:27,910 --> 00:19:30,340
What if she runs away
and acts out again like last time?

295
00:19:30,410 --> 00:19:33,340
She's had her warning shot.
She won't do that this time.

296
00:19:33,410 --> 00:19:36,380
You really know Seo Rin well, Chairman.

297
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:40,580
My mom and I have been
so lonely for so long,

298
00:19:40,950 --> 00:19:42,690
I'm just so happy...

299
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:44,420
to have a family like this.

300
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:49,130
May I call you Father?

301
00:19:49,130 --> 00:19:50,290
Shut up, Jin Hong Ju.

302
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:54,400
Of course. He's your father now,
you should call him that.

303
00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:55,930
What else would you call him?

304
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,340
Isn't that right, darling?

305
00:19:59,570 --> 00:20:02,040
It's nice to suddenly have a daughter.

306
00:20:04,910 --> 00:20:05,910
CEO Chae.

307
00:20:07,610 --> 00:20:10,080
Oh my goodness. Force of habit.

308
00:20:11,950 --> 00:20:14,990
I wonder what I should call you
from now on.

309
00:20:15,790 --> 00:20:16,850
Seo Rin's mom?

310
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:19,190
My little daughter-in-law?

311
00:20:19,190 --> 00:20:20,460
Is she out of her mind?

312
00:20:20,860 --> 00:20:22,160
She's rubbing it in.

313
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:25,100
All the mistreatment I got from you,

314
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,100
I'll make you pay, little by little.

315
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:28,600
Just you wait, Chae Hwa Young.

316
00:20:30,770 --> 00:20:32,840
Now that we're all a family,

317
00:20:33,340 --> 00:20:37,640
let's all cherish and love one another
from now on.

318
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:40,110
Yes, let's do that.

319
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:41,950
Father!

320
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:44,310
I cannot approve of this marriage.

321
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:47,320
No, it's not even a marriage.
You're just moving in together.

322
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:49,250
And I can't approve of that either.

323
00:20:50,150 --> 00:20:52,120
- Why not?
- San Wol is my friend.

324
00:20:52,420 --> 00:20:56,060
If word gets out at Dream Group,
it'll immediately affect our stock price.

325
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:59,330
Do you hate the idea of your father-in-law
being happy that much?

326
00:20:59,460 --> 00:21:02,170
Why are you trying to rain on our parade
with all this talk about stock prices?

327
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:04,740
Yeom San Wol! Shut your mouth!

328
00:21:05,340 --> 00:21:09,410
Imagine if rumors spread that a woman
who is my friend since elementary school,

329
00:21:09,540 --> 00:21:13,310
is living with the chairman
of Dream Group.

330
00:21:13,510 --> 00:21:15,280
The gossipmongers will have a field day,
of course.

331
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:17,110
It'll be all over the tabloids,

332
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:20,580
and even our loyal customers
will be gossiping about it.

333
00:21:20,650 --> 00:21:24,990
It's a marriage, not just "moving in."
Let's call it what it is.

334
00:21:25,060 --> 00:21:27,190
Don't you think all that will be reflected
in the stock price?

335
00:21:27,690 --> 00:21:30,330
You have to consider the reputation
of Dream Group, Father.

336
00:21:30,630 --> 00:21:34,360
- That woman once carried my purse...
- Enough!

337
00:21:34,430 --> 00:21:35,970
- Father.
- I've heard enough!

338
00:21:36,270 --> 00:21:37,730
I don't need any more explanations.

339
00:21:38,370 --> 00:21:40,670
That's why I've been walking on eggshells
around you and waiting all this time.

340
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:43,410
Do you have any idea how old I am?

341
00:21:43,540 --> 00:21:48,080
Father, this is all the more reason
you must maintain your dignity.

342
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:50,450
If you're truly that lonely, Father,

343
00:21:51,050 --> 00:21:54,950
I will find you a suitable match,
someone of your stature.

344
00:21:55,190 --> 00:21:58,620
That way we can ally with a family
that will benefit Dream Group.

345
00:21:59,060 --> 00:22:00,720
Will the board stand by?

346
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:02,790
- Don't you think, Father?
- Chae Hwa Young.

347
00:22:03,330 --> 00:22:06,560
So you're saying I'm completely
beneath his class?

348
00:22:07,130 --> 00:22:09,730
I've had enough of this.
This is just too insulting.

349
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:12,300
As if you were born with a silver spoon
in your mouth.

350
00:22:12,870 --> 00:22:17,440
Bad enough I carried your bags for years
and waited on you hand and foot,

351
00:22:18,010 --> 00:22:19,980
but now I have to take this treatment
from you?

352
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:23,410
- Know your place.
- You're going too far, ma'am.

353
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,720
That's enough.

354
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:28,590
CEO Chae, no matter what you say,
my mind is made up.

355
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,820
This woman is mine now,
and you will accept that.

356
00:22:31,190 --> 00:22:34,160
And from this day forward,
Hong Ju is my daughter.

357
00:22:34,490 --> 00:22:36,430
So you will treat her with the respect
she deserves.

358
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:53,340
How could you be my mother-in-law?

359
00:22:53,340 --> 00:22:54,340
How?

360
00:22:55,980 --> 00:22:59,450
This is insane. I will never accept this.

361
00:23:02,350 --> 00:23:03,620
Then...

362
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:06,520
that witch San Wol
and her daughter Hong Ju...

363
00:23:07,060 --> 00:23:08,690
will get the company shares.

364
00:23:08,690 --> 00:23:11,930
No, they'll fight tooth and nail
to get their hands on company shares.

365
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,200
I can't just stand by
and let them take it.

366
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:18,070
That's it.

367
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:21,470
I have to get Jun Ho and Seo Rin
married right away.

368
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:26,040
I have to make sure
Jun Ho gets control of Dream right away.

369
00:23:34,990 --> 00:23:36,020
Yes.

370
00:23:38,190 --> 00:23:39,260
Really?

371
00:23:39,420 --> 00:23:40,520
I see.

372
00:23:41,660 --> 00:23:42,760
Is it true...

373
00:23:43,030 --> 00:23:45,360
that Professor Kang Nam Bong who was
in charge of renovating Dream Hotel...

374
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:46,630
caused a car crash?

375
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:47,900
Did he?

376
00:23:48,730 --> 00:23:52,340
Yes. Apparently, a drunk person was
in the middle of the road.

377
00:23:52,940 --> 00:23:56,410
He called 911 right away,
and it looks like he turned himself in.

378
00:23:56,510 --> 00:23:59,680
- What a stroke of bad luck.
- Professor Kang Nam Bong?

379
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:01,110
This is my son.

380
00:24:01,210 --> 00:24:03,050
Say hello. She's the CEO of this hotel.

381
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:06,380
Yes, hello. We've actually met before.

382
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,250
You're right.

383
00:24:08,250 --> 00:24:09,850
You did look a little familiar.

384
00:24:10,190 --> 00:24:13,420
You're the lawyer
who came with that aspiring singer.

385
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:15,090
Yes, I'm Kang Baek Ho.

386
00:24:16,930 --> 00:24:19,460
That's right!
He's the guy from last night.

387
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:22,800
Kang Baek Ho. What was he doing there?

388
00:24:25,170 --> 00:24:27,800
You sure are full of surprises.

389
00:24:28,140 --> 00:24:29,140
Excuse me?

390
00:24:29,140 --> 00:24:30,470
A handshake? The nerve.

391
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:35,650
That's it. He must have mistaken me
for Oh Jang Mi.

392
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:40,320
You want me to get them
to sign a settlement?

393
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:41,690
That's right.

394
00:24:42,020 --> 00:24:43,990
It's not like your father
did anything that wrong.

395
00:24:44,890 --> 00:24:46,590
It was just a case of bad luck.

396
00:24:47,820 --> 00:24:51,430
So you should go and ask them
to sign the settlement agreement.

397
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,200
Mom, that's not right.

398
00:24:53,730 --> 00:24:56,030
How am I supposed to ask Jang Mi
to sign a settlement?

399
00:24:56,100 --> 00:24:57,100
Kang Baek Ho!

400
00:24:57,100 --> 00:25:00,140
Is Oh Jang Mi
more important than your own father?

401
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:02,170
Aren't you worried
about your father at all?

402
00:25:02,610 --> 00:25:03,640
Oh Jang Mi?

403
00:25:04,370 --> 00:25:05,580
A settlement? What's that about?

404
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:06,840
Mom.

405
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:10,680
First, Dad should go to the hospital
and apologize to Jang Mi's father.

406
00:25:10,750 --> 00:25:12,420
The settlement agreement can wait.

407
00:25:13,150 --> 00:25:15,390
Right now, Jang Mi's father
is fighting for his life.

408
00:25:15,450 --> 00:25:17,750
I know,

409
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:22,360
but we'll be in a much better position
if we get the settlement before he dies.

410
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:26,360
Oh my gosh! So Professor Kang Nam Bong
hit Oh Jang Mi's dad?

411
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:47,120
Are you all right?

412
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:49,350
Yes, I'm fine.

413
00:25:49,990 --> 00:25:52,290
Shouldn't you go see a doctor?

414
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:53,590
No, I'm fine.

415
00:25:54,190 --> 00:25:56,790
I've just been
under a lot of stress lately.

416
00:25:57,790 --> 00:26:00,930
I'm sorry. You just missed Baek Ho.
He stepped out a minute ago.

417
00:26:01,930 --> 00:26:04,470
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to overhear.

418
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:08,610
It sounds like Professor Kang Nam Bong
is in some trouble.

419
00:26:15,450 --> 00:26:16,880
This has to be the place.

420
00:26:17,610 --> 00:26:18,920
"Law Firm Leeho."

421
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:22,550
"Lawyer Kang Baek Ho
and Han Young Ja's office."

422
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:27,020
Jin Hong Ju?

423
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:28,890
What's she doing there?

424
00:26:30,260 --> 00:26:33,930
Hong Ju, you have feelings
for my Baek Ho, don't you?

425
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:35,900
Yes, I do.

426
00:26:36,530 --> 00:26:40,140
But Baek Ho likes the girl
from the side dish shop, doesn't he?

427
00:26:40,940 --> 00:26:44,710
It's so upsetting he got mixed up
with Oh Jang Mi in this whole mess.

428
00:26:46,140 --> 00:26:47,840
Talk about a terrible twist of fate.

429
00:26:48,350 --> 00:26:52,150
Of all the people for my husband to hit,
it had to be Oh Jang Mi's father.

430
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:54,050
I'm just so frustrated.

431
00:26:54,580 --> 00:26:57,220
You have to stop Baek Ho.

432
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,560
They can't be together
now that their families are enemies.

433
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:01,360
No way!

434
00:27:01,930 --> 00:27:04,260
The person Professor Kang hit
was Oh Jang Mi's dad?

435
00:27:05,100 --> 00:27:07,130
What is this crazy connection
between me and Oh Jang Mi?

436
00:27:07,900 --> 00:27:09,000
Could we actually be twins?

437
00:27:22,710 --> 00:27:23,710
God.

438
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:27,050
Please save my dad.

439
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:30,620
My poor dad.

440
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:41,360
Dad? Are you awake?

441
00:27:53,910 --> 00:27:55,110
Jang Mi...

442
00:28:07,190 --> 00:28:08,260
Mom!

443
00:28:09,130 --> 00:28:10,190
Am I a twin?

444
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:13,200
I'm asking, am I a twin?

445
00:28:19,540 --> 00:28:20,540
Dad.

446
00:28:24,110 --> 00:28:25,310
Dad!

447
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:27,780
Dad!

448
00:28:53,770 --> 00:28:55,770
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
